This paper is likely to belong to the Control Systems (cs.SY) sub-category as it focuses on feedback control and closed-loop stability. It also involves the coordination of multiple physical systems, which could fall under the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of a wireless network suggests that it could also be relevant to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper's emphasis on dynamic changes between different sets of application tasks and the use of embedded devices suggests that it could be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.MA) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on cyber-physical systems and the use of wireless networks could also make it relevant to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category.
